oard Resources The UICOMR Blackboard site provides a wealth of information and links to guide the student through the process  The site is located within the Clerkship  Careers in Medicine Resources CiM  self assessments and resources  CiM is designed to help students make an informed decision about specialty and to provide guidelines for future career choices Careers in Medicine  Medical Student Performance Evaluation  MSPE Medical Student Performance Evaluations   Beginning in the summer of the M  year  students make consultation appointments with the Assistant Dean for Student Affairs to help with development of the MSPE  As such  it includes  Education MD Admissions Rockford Interviews MD Curriculum Campus Specific Programs Clinician Executive Medicine Program  CE MED James Scholar Program for Independent Study Rural Medical Education  RMED  Program Curriculum by Year M  Year M  Year M  and M  Years Psychiatry Clerkship Course Management Blackboard Exams Benware Course Evaluations Visiting Students Medical Education and Evaluation MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Staff Academic Skills Step   Resources Housing Computing Registrar Career Services Scholarship Opportunities Student Financial Planning Student Health and Wellness MD Student Life Rockford Resources Student Organizations Parking   Transportation Diversity Educational Policies Master of Science in Medical Biotechnology Program Master of Science in Medical Biotechnology Program Start a Career Through the MBT Program Admissions Information and Requirements FAQs Guaranteed Admission Program Agreement Curriculum Overview Tuition and Fees Contact Information MBT Contact Me Form MBT Faculty and Staff MBT Photo Gallery Testimonials Graduate Medical Education  GME Family Medicine Residency Welcome Where are our graduates now  Policies Manual Career and Life Planning for Residents Rockford Family Medicine Residency Program Curriculum First Year Residency Second Year Residency Third Year Residency S